page.content: for a pint at the local. Local newspapers reported 17th. November1894 as the day that{Cookham}almost sank. {Cookham The solitary figure of the local {Tarrystone Sits in{Cookham High St.}It cannot move or roam. After the sun sets you can't hear a sound, Not even a car in the narrow{Pound. Up to the{Rise,}past a small shop, Up at the crossing the train makes you stop. Down the road and into the Dean It's the prettiest sight that I've ever seen. {Cookham}stops here_it's really quite small. But{Cookham's}not bad to live in at all. {Christopher Copland.
